<subSubSection id="C31B653CA969196CAFB9F9DA43B06241" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A969196CAFB9F9DA43B06241" blockId="8.[151,1437,1446,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A969196CAFB9F9DA46DF6219" bold="true" box="[199,468,1554,1580]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differentiated from other Peruvian species by the combination of the moderate body size (ca. 
<quantity id="4CF99B52A969196CAF82F9FE466E6264" box="[252,357,1590,1617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.50 mm</quantity>
), the rather large head (width greater than width or length of pronotum), and the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="133A2A32A969196CAFDEF99247EF6241" box="[160,228,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[170,1426,470,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-121@9.[151,1435,453,1956]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hydrochus bucapitus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4417295" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4417295/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
; described below). Completely reliable determinations will include dissection of males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B653CA969196EAFB9F9B647DC64CC" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A969196CAFB9F9B647E96345" blockId="8.[151,1437,1446,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A969196CAFB9F9B6465A62AD" bold="true" box="[199,337,1662,1688]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Description</emphasis>
. Habitus as illustrated (
<figureCitation id="133A2A32A969196CAD23F9B645A962AC" box="[605,674,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[170,1426,470,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-121@9.[151,1435,453,1956]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hydrochus bucapitus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4417295" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4417295/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Size: 
<typeStatus id="54BA8815A969196CAD89F9B6445262AD" box="[759,857,1662,1688]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">holotype</typeStatus>
(length/width, mm): body (length to elytral apices) 2.50/0.83; head width 0.62; pronotum l/w 0.58/0.55; PA 0.55; PB 0.42; elytra 1.60/0.83. Body size moderate (ca. 
<quantity id="4CF99B52A969196CAFE9F90E460962D4" box="[151,258,1734,1761]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.50 mm</quantity>
), very narrow, except head relatively wide. Dorsum dark brown with slight iridescence, elytra without black spots. Dorsum with numerous microsetae. Legs testaceous, with tibiofemoral joints and basal ½ of femora darker. Punctation on elytra ca. 2–4x that of pronotum. Elytra interstriae narrow walls to ca. 0.5x strial puncture diameter. Interstria 9 
<superScript id="7C749BFFA969196CAEFEF8FA46866375" attach="left" box="[384,397,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">th</superScript>
more convex than others, overhanging 10 
<superScript id="7C749BFFA969196CAC1AF8FA447A6375" attach="left" box="[868,881,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">th</superScript>
interstria. Usual area of callus on 5 
<superScript id="7C749BFFA969196CAB81F8FA42076375" attach="left" box="[1279,1292,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">th</superScript>
very weakly raised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A969196CAFB9F8B3456163E8" blockId="8.[151,1437,1446,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Pronotum very slightly longer than wide, widest at anterior margin, narrowed at base, sides very weakly arcuate, almost straight, smooth; anterior margin arcuate; depressions moderately deep, coarsely densely punctate, reliefs between depressions less punctate.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A968196DAFB9FF5F430664E0" blockId="9.[151,1436,150,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Elytra with spaces between strial punctures narrow walls to ca. 0.5x their diameter; apices rather sharply conjointly rounded in dorsal view, in lateral view outer margin without angulation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A968196DAFB9FF1746C56528" blockId="9.[151,1436,150,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Ventral characters: Mentum moderately densely finely punctate, with large, deep median fovea. Submentum with two large deep foveae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A968196DAFB9FEEF44DE6598" blockId="9.[151,1436,150,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="133A2A32A968196DAE02FEEF46CA6577" box="[380,449,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[170,1426,470,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-121@9.[151,1435,453,1956]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hydrochus bucapitus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4417295" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4417295/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) general characters: genitalia very small, very slender, length ca. 6x width; parameres pointed in dorsal/ventral views and lateral view, only slightly longer than aedeagus, lacking plsa; aedeagus narrowly lanceolate, agw at about midlength; basal piece slightly shorter than parameres, width ca. equal in dorsal/ventral and lateral views, orifice sclerotized, inverted V-shape in dorsal/ventral views.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7E663FA968196DAFE9F87344C363E6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4417295" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4417295" box="[151,968,1979,2003]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4417295/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" startId="9.[151,250,1979,2003]" targetBox="[170,1426,470,1941]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A968196DAFE9F87344C363E6" blockId="9.[151,968,1979,2003]" box="[151,968,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A968196DAFE9F873461863E6" bold="true" box="[151,275,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C014D34A968196DAE67F87346FA63E6" authority="Perkins, 2020" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2020" box="[281,497,1979,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucapitus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A968196DAE67F87346FA63E6" box="[281,497,1979,2003]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Hydrochus bucapitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A968196DAE89F873453B63E6" bold="true" box="[503,560,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24657DEA968196DAE89F873453B63E6" box="[503,560,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, habitus and male genitalia of holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A96B196EAFB9FF5F442B6484" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,800,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Dorsal surface: adbl large; pdmm approximating alm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A96B196EAFB9FF7347DC64CC" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Ventral surface: pvmm over middle ½ overlapping aedeagus, margins very narrowly separated one from the other.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B653CA96B196EAFB9FECB44616528" box="[199,874,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBE36B7A96B196EAFB9FECB44616528" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,874,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B975EAA5A96B196EAFB9FECB46456528" bold="true" box="[199,334,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in reference to the relatively large head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
